sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id)
FROM Author a
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN Citation c ON al.paper_id = c.cited_paper_id
    WHERE al.author_id = a.author_id
    GROUP BY al.paper_id
    HAVING COUNT(c.paper_id) > 50
)
question: How many authors have not published a paper with more than 50 citations?

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id)
FROM Author a
WHERE a.author_id NOT IN (
    SELECT al.author_id
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN (
        SELECT c.paper_id
        FROM Citation c
        GROUP BY c.paper_id
        HAVING COUNT(*) > 50
    ) high_cited ON al.paper_id = high_cited.paper_id
)

sql:

FROM Author a
WHERE a.author_id NOT IN (
    SELECT al.author_id
    FROM Author_list al
    JOIN Citation c ON al.paper_id = c.cited_paper_id
    GROUP BY al.paper_id, al.author_id
    HAVING COUNT(c.paper_id) > 50
)

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.author_id)
FROM Author a
LEFT JOIN Author_list al ON a.author_id = al.author_id
LEFT JOIN Paper p ON al.paper_id = p.paper_id
LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT c.paper_id, COUNT(*) AS citation_count
    FROM Citation c
    GROUP BY c.paper_id
) pc ON p.paper_id = pc.paper_id
GROUP BY a.author_id
HAVING MAX(COALESCE(pc.citation_count, 0)) <= 50;
question: How many authors have not published a paper with more than 50 citations?
